        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 1:13AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 112 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Kolola Springs, or 8 miles southeast of Aberdeen,
moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amory, Aberdeen, Prairie, Hatley, Gattman, Binford, New Hamilton,
Becker, Quincy, Wise Gap, Athens, Wren, Strong, East Aberdeen,
Muldon, and Greenwood Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
northeastern Mississippi.</instruction>
